Memory-augmented evolution: changes and usage

Summary of changes
- Added memory prompt injection via program metadata key "mutation_memory" so extra instructions are appended to the mutation prompt when present. (gigaevo/llm/agents/mutation.py, gigaevo/evolution/mutation/context.py)
- Added memory-augmented mutation path in the evolution engine that:
  - reads instructions from memory.txt or memory/*.json each generation
  - selects top-N programs by primary fitness
  - generates additional mutations with memory attached
  (gigaevo/evolution/engine/core.py)
- Added mutation persistence tags so every child program is labeled with metadata_memory_used in Redis/CSV. (gigaevo/evolution/engine/mutation.py)
- Added config switches to enable/disable memory, set top-N, and point to a memory file (.txt or .json). (gigaevo/evolution/engine/config.py, config/constants/evolution.yaml, config/evolution/default.yaml)

How to run an experiment with memory enabled
1) Ensure the memory file exists (txt or json):
   /home/petranokhin/projects/giga_evo1/gigaevo-core-internal/memory/memory_26.json
   (Edit it to include any instructions you want appended to mutation prompts.)

2) Run the experiment with memory enabled (example):
   python run.py problem.name=<your_problem> memory_enabled=true memory_top_n=5

Optional overrides
- memory_path: Path to the memory instructions file
  Example: python run.py memory_enabled=true memory_path=/abs/path/to/memory_26.json
- memory_top_n: Number of top programs (by primary fitness) used to seed memory mutations
- memory_enabled: false disables memory augmentation entirely

CSV logging note
- The memory flag is stored as program metadata and appears as:
  metadata_memory_used
  when exporting with tools/redis2pd.py (or any exporter that includes metadata_* columns).
